#!/usr/bin/env ssc
# Use Crypto Plugin

Demonstrates calling `extern def` functions provided by the
`org.example.crypto` plugin.

```scala
import [Crypto](crypto)

val digest   = sha256("hello, world")
val encoded  = base64Encode("hello")
val decoded  = base64Decode(encoded)
val mac      = hmacSha256("secret-key", "message")

println("sha256:        " + digest)
println("base64:        " + encoded)
println("decoded:       " + decoded)
println("hmac-sha256:   " + mac)
```
